Regular Heatmap

plot_fig1.knit

load the data

rm(list = ls())
library(forestplot)
library(dplyr)
library(pheatmap)
library(RColorBrewer)

# '20230515_covid_regional_contex.csv' or '20230515_covid_left_right_subcortex.csv'
file_path <- '20230515_covid_left_right_subcortex.csv' 
measure_label <- 'volumn' # 'thickavg' or 'surfavg' or 'volumn'

data <- read.csv(file_path, header = TRUE)
head(data[c('exposure', 'outcome', 'method', 'b', 'se.x', 'pval.x')])

## 2 Covid infection          Brain.stem                  MR Egger -0.017836714
## 3 Covid infection          Brain.stem           Weighted median -0.012797067
## 4 Covid infection left.accumbens.area Inverse variance weighted  0.028352371
## 5 Covid infection left.accumbens.area                  MR Egger  0.036179417
## 6 Covid infection left.accumbens.area           Weighted median  0.029585339
##         se.x    pval.x
## 1 0.04553056 0.9336514
## 2 0.10800493 0.8768384
## 3 0.05361871 0.8113631
## 4 0.05489680 0.6055285
## 5 0.12231116 0.7821046
## 6 0.06515554 0.6497766

process data

data_infection <- data |> filter(exposure=='Covid infection')
data_severity <- data |> filter(exposure=='Covid severity')

data_infection <- data_infection |>
  filter(measurement == measure_label) |>   #'thickness', 'surface area'
  filter(method == 'Inverse variance weighted')

data_severity <- data_severity |>
  filter(measurement == measure_label) |>   #'thickness', 'surface area'
  filter(method == 'Inverse variance weighted')

data_plot <- data.frame(row.names = data_severity$outcome)
data_plot$infection <- data_infection$b/data_infection$se.x
data_plot$severity <- data_severity$b/data_severity$se.x

data_p <- data.frame(row.names = data_severity$outcome)
data_p$infection <- data_infection$pval.x
data_p$severity <- data_severity$pval.x

head(data_p)
##                     infection  severity
## Brain.stem          0.9336514 0.9055478
## left.accumbens.area 0.6055285 0.8713543
## left.amygdala       0.4501532 0.8772266
## left.caudate        0.6982444 0.5947670
## left.hippocampus    0.9169623 0.6035164
## left.insula         0.7867675 0.5811359

plot the figure

bk <- c(seq(-1.5,-0.01,by=0.01),seq(0,1.5,by=0.01))
pheatmap(as.data.frame(t(data_plot)),
         breaks = bk,
         legend_breaks=seq(-1.5,1.5,0.5),
         legend_labels = c("-1.5","-1","-0.5","0","0.5","1","1.5"),
         color = colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(n = 7, 
                                                 name = "RdYlBu")))(length(bk)),
         cluster_cols = FALSE,
         cluster_rows = FALSE,
         #display_numbers = matrix(ifelse(data_p < 0.05, "*", ""), nrow(data_p)),
         fontsize_number = 12,
         fontsize_row = 12,
         angle_col = "315",
         #annotation_colors = "white",
         number_color = "black",
         name = "Z-Score")

Circle Heatmap

plot_fig2.knit

load data

rm(list = ls())
library(ComplexHeatmap)
library(circlize)
library(RColorBrewer)

data_global <- read.csv('20230515_dna_covid_global_cortex.csv') 
data_global <- data_global[data_global$method == 'Inverse variance weighted',]
data_global$group <- 'Global'

data_regional <- read.csv('20230515_dna_covid_regional_contex.csv') 
data_regional <- data_regional[data_regional$method == 'Inverse variance weighted',]
data_regional$group <- 'Regional'

data_left_right <- read.csv('20230515_dna_covid_left_right_subcortex.csv') 
data_left_right <- data_left_right[data_left_right$method == 'Inverse variance weighted',]
data_left_right$group <- 'Left Right'

data_combined <- read.csv('20230515_dna_covid_combined_subcortex.csv') 
data_combined <- data_combined[data_combined$method == 'Inverse variance weighted',]
data_combined$group <- 'Combined'

process data

data_combined <- data_combined[c('outcome','exposure','b','se', 'group')]
data_combined$Z_score <- data_combined$b/data_combined$se
data_global <- data_global[c('outcome','exposure','b','se', 'group')]
data_global$Z_score <- data_global$b/data_global$se
data_regional <- data_regional[c('outcome','exposure','b','se', 'group')]
data_regional$Z_score <- data_regional$b/data_regional$se
data_left_right <- data_left_right[c('outcome','exposure','b','se', 'group')]
data_left_right$Z_score <- data_left_right$b/data_left_right$se

exposure_list <- list("COVID-19 positive vs COVID-19 negative or COVID-19 status unknown",
                      "COVID-19 positive not hospitalized vs COVID-19 negative or COVID-19 status unknown",
                      "COVID-19 positive vs COVID-19 negative",
                      "COVID-19 positive hospitalized vs COVID-19 positive not hospitalized",
                      "COVID-19 positive hospitalized vs COVID-19 negative or COVID-19 status unknown",
                      "COVID-19 positive severe vs COVID-19 negative or COVID-19 status unknown")

exposure1 <- exposure_list[1]
global_infection1 <- data_global[data_global$exposure == exposure1,]
regional_infection1 <- data_regional[data_regional$exposure == exposure1,]
combined_infection1 <- data_combined[data_combined$exposure == exposure1,]
left_right_infection1 <- data_left_right[data_left_right$exposure == exposure1,]
dat_inf1 <- rbind(global_infection1,regional_infection1,combined_infection1,left_right_infection1)
dat_infection1 <- data.frame(row.names = dat_inf1$outcome,
                             dat_inf1[c('Z_score','group')])
colnames(dat_infection1) <- c(exposure1,'group')

dat_all <- data.frame(row.names = dat_infection1)

for (exposure1 in exposure_list) {
  global_infection1 <- data_global[data_global$exposure == exposure1,]
  regional_infection1 <- data_regional[data_regional$exposure == exposure1,]
  combined_infection1 <- data_combined[data_combined$exposure == exposure1,]
  left_right_infection1 <- data_left_right[data_left_right$exposure == exposure1,]
  dat_1 <- rbind(global_infection1,regional_infection1,combined_infection1,left_right_infection1)
  dat_1 <- data.frame(row.names = dat_1$outcome, 
                      dat_1$Z_score)
  colnames(dat_1) <- exposure1
  dat_all <- cbind(dat_all, dat_1)
}

split <- factor(dat_infection1$group, levels = c("Global", "Regional", "Left Right", "Combined"))

dat_all <- as.matrix(dat_all)

head(dat_all)

plot figure

circos.clear()

color = colorRampPalette(rev(brewer.pal(n = 7, 
                                        name = "RdYlBu")))(401)
col_fun1 = colorRamp2(seq(-2,2,0.01), color)
circos.par(start.degree = 90, gap.degree = 10)

circos.heatmap(as.matrix(dat_all[,1]), split = split, col = col_fun1, track.height = 0.05,
               show.sector.labels = TRUE)
circos.heatmap(as.matrix(dat_all[,2]), split = split, col = col_fun1, track.height = 0.05,
               show.sector.labels = TRUE)
circos.heatmap(as.matrix(dat_all[,3]), split = split, col = col_fun1, track.height = 0.05,
               rownames.side = "inside",
               show.sector.labels = TRUE)

circos.heatmap(as.matrix(dat_all[,4]), split = split, col = col_fun1, track.height = 0.05,
               show.sector.labels = TRUE)
circos.heatmap(as.matrix(dat_all[,5]), split = split, col = col_fun1, track.height = 0.05,
               show.sector.labels = TRUE)
circos.heatmap(as.matrix(dat_all[,6]), split = split, col = col_fun1, track.height = 0.05,
               show.sector.labels = TRUE)

# add legend
lgd = Legend(title = "Z Score", col_fun = col_fun1)
grid.draw(lgd)

Forest Plots

Regular Forest Plots

plot_fig2.knit 
rm(list = ls())
library(forestplot)
library(dplyr)

data1 <- read.csv("plot2a.csv")
data1 <- data1[data1$method == 'Inverse variance weighted',]
data1 <- data1[c('exposure', 'outcome', 'or', 'or_lci95', 'or_uci95')]
colnames(data1) <- c('labeltext', 'group', 'mean', 'lower', 'upper')
head(data1)
##                labeltext                                 group      mean
## 1   SARS-CoV-2 infection           1Cortical amyloid beta load 1.0470051
## 2  Hospitalized COVID-19           1Cortical amyloid beta load 1.0169914
## 3      Critical COVID-19           1Cortical amyloid beta load 1.0109526
## 6   SARS-CoV-2 infection 2Alzheimers disease progression score 0.9886282
## 9  Hospitalized COVID-19 2Alzheimers disease progression score 1.0002756
## 12     Critical COVID-19 2Alzheimers disease progression score 0.9996817
##        lower    upper
## 1  0.6807174 1.610389
## 2  0.9113855 1.134834
## 3  0.9425631 1.084304
## 6  0.8364508 1.168492
## 9  0.9588436 1.043498
## 12 0.9731772 1.026908
fp1 <- data1 |> 
  group_by(group) |>
  forestplot(
    clip = c(0.6, 1.6),
    xticks = c(0.6, 0.8, 1.0, 1.2, 1.4, 1.6),
    ci.vertices = TRUE,
    ci.vertices.height = 0.05,
    boxsize = .1,
    xlab = "OR (95% CI)",
    zero = 1,
    title = "                           HGI COVID-19",
    legend = c("Cortical amyloid beta load", "Alzheimers disease progression score", "Hippocampal volume"),
    #legend_args = fpLegend(pos = list("topright")),
    col = fpColors(box = c("darkblue", "darkred", "darkgreen"),
                   line = c("darkblue", "darkred", "darkgreen")))
plot(fp1)

Forest Plots with Groups

plot_fig1.knit 
rm(list = ls())
library(forestplot)
library(dplyr)

data1 <- read.csv("plot1a.csv")
data1 <- data1[data1$method == 'Inverse variance weighted',]
data1 <- data1[c('exposure',  'or', 'or_lci95', 'or_uci95', 'pval')]
colnames(data1) <- c('labeltext',  'mean', 'lower', 'upper', 'pval')
head(data1)
##                labeltext      mean     lower    upper      pval
## 1   SARS-CoV-2 infection 0.9790143 0.8076468 1.186743 0.8289608
## 4  Hospitalized COVID-19 0.9815525 0.9000865 1.070392 0.6736081
## 7      Critical COVID-19 0.9755567 0.9239442 1.030052 0.3722147
## 10    Critical COVID-19* 0.9776869 0.9246905 1.033721 0.4274140
or_text1 <- c()
p_text1 <- c()
for (i in 1:dim(data1)[1]) {
  or_temp <- paste(as.character(round(data1$mean[i],3)), '(', 
                   as.character(round(data1$lower[i],3)),',',
                   as.character(round(data1$upper[i],3)),')', sep = '')
  or_text1 <- c(or_text1, or_temp)
  
  p_text1 <- c(p_text1, as.character(round(data1$pval[i],3)))
}

base_data1 <- tibble(mean=data1$mean,
                     lower=data1$lower,
                     upper=data1$upper, 
                     OR=or_text1,
                     p=p_text1,
                     exp_v=data1$labeltext)


header1 <- tibble(OR=c("OR"),
                 exp_v=c("Exposure"),
                 p=c("P"),
                 summary=TRUE)
dis_row1 <- tibble(OR=c(NA),
                  exp_v=c('Discovery'),
                  p=c(NA),
                  summary=TRUE)

output_df1 <- bind_rows(header1, dis_row1, 
                       base_data1)


fp1 <- output_df1 |>
  forestplot(labeltext=c(exp_v, OR, p),
             is.summary=summary,
             shapes_gp = fpShapesGp(box = c("blue") |> lapply(function(x) gpar(fill = x, col = "#555555")),
                                    default = gpar(vertices = TRUE)),
             clip=c(0.97,1.03),
             boxsize=.2,
             #xlog=TRUE,
             zero = 1,
             xticks = c(0.91, 1.0, 1.09),
             graph.pos = 3,
             hrzl_lines = list("2" = gpar(lty = 1)),
             col = fpColors(box = "royalblue",
                            line = "darkblue",
                            summary = "royalblue"),
             xlab = "OR",
             vertices = TRUE)
plot(fp1)
